      <back>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Tel Sandahannah is located 1.5 km from Marisa (Beth Govrin). The ancient city of Marisa occupied the high mound, a lower city with ancillary cave complexes, and a cemetery. This inscription was found on the slopes of the hill. The fragment that contains the inscription is part of a base of a fragmentary statue of an eagle, of which only one claw is preserved. The inscription is in two lines, of which only the right halves remain intact.</p>
         </div>
